      "parent_block_plain_text": "Nvidia’s X800-Q3450 CPO switch features 115.2T total throughput and is designed for use with the scale-out network. The initial version will use 72 optical engines each operating at 1.6Tbit/s; later versions will likely transition to 36 optical engines at 3.2Tbit/s each, costing ~$1,000 per unit (including FAUs). As a result, the total BOM cost for the optical engines amounts to around $35-40k (for the 3.2T OE version).",
